SIMPLE: astony
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Astony
<hw>As*ton"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Astonied</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Astonying</conjf>. See <er>Astone</er>.]</vmorph>
<def>To stun; to bewilder; to astonish; to dismay.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The captain of the Helots . . . strake Palladius upon the side of
his head, that he reeled <qex>astonied</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This sodeyn cas this man <qex>astonied</qex> so,⟦br⟧
That reed he wex, abayst, and al quaking.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Astoop</ent>⟦br⟧
